# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WiiM Universal Remote -- environment
# Headless service: no database, no sessions, no login.
#
# Every setting here is optional. An empty .env file works fine.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Remote access control ------------------------------------------------
# The trust model is LAN-trust: a hardware remote fires bare GETs and cannot
# log in. Leave REMOTE_TOKEN unset and the routes are open to anything that
# can reach the port -- fine on a trusted LAN, NOT fine if this port is
# exposed to the internet. Set it to require ?token=... or an X-Remote-Token
# header on every request.
# REMOTE_TOKEN=

# --- WiiM device TLS (optional) -------------------------------------------
# Most WiiM units accept plain TLS with verification disabled (the default).
# A few newer firmwares require the LinkPlay mutual-TLS client certificate.
# If a device refuses the TLS handshake, bind-mount the PEMs and set these.
# WIIM_CLIENT_CERT_PATH=/certs/linkplay-client.crt
# WIIM_CLIENT_KEY_PATH=/certs/linkplay-client.key
